    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1974-05-31T09:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1974-05-31T07:33:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <head>207. Memorandum of Conversation<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d207fn1"
                        >Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>
                        Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, Box 1029,
                            <gloss target="#t_Memcon1">MemCon</gloss>s—<gloss target="#t_HAK1"
                            >HAK</gloss> &amp; Presidential. Secret; <gloss target="#t_Nodis1"
                            >Nodis</gloss>. The conversation took place in the Oval Office.
                        According to the President’s Daily Diary, the meeting was held over
                        breakfast from 8:33 to 10:25 a.m. (Ibid., White House Central Files,
                        President’s Daily Diary)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_imprecise-inferred-from-editorial-annotation"
                            calendar="gregorian" from="1974-05-31T08:33:00-04:00"
                            to="1974-05-31T10:25:00-04:00" type="conversation-or-meeting-date">May
                            31, 1974</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>PARTICIPANTS</head>
                    <item>President <persName corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Dr. <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>, Assistant
                        to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                    <pb facs="0668" n="633" xml:id="pg_633"/>
                    <item>General <persName corresp="#p_HBMJ1">Alexander M. Haig, Jr.</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>Major General <persName corresp="#p_SB3">Brent Scowcroft</persName>,
                        Deputy Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Report on Secretary <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>’s
                        Middle East Trip and President’s Forthcoming</item>
                    <item>Trips to the Middle East and <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>: On <gloss target="#t_SALT1"
                        >SALT</gloss>, maybe an agreement in principle is possible. On <gloss
                        target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>. …</p>
                <p>President: Which would have enormous domestic impact.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>: … a 5% <gloss target="#t_US1"
                        >US</gloss>-Soviet cut is conceivable.</p>
                <p>President: We should lay the groundwork with the Soviet Union.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>: That could give minor problems
                    with the Europeans. The Soviet Union is waiting to see how <gloss
                        target="#t_CSCE1">CSCE</gloss> works out. We are holding up <gloss
                        target="#t_CSCE1">CSCE</gloss> until you get to Moscow.</p>
                <p>Maybe you can get something in <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss> for <gloss
                        target="#t_CSCE1">CSCE</gloss>.</p>
                <p>President: We want to show new progress on <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>
                    to avert unilateral cuts here.</p>
                <p>[Omitted here is discussion of matters other than the European security
                    conference or <gloss target="#t_MBFR1">MBFR</gloss>.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
